definition.value: A piece of chicken skin.
A whole wing that is obtained from a chicken.
The wing of a chicken
Buffalo wings, invented in Buffalo, New York, are chicken wings that are generally deep-fried then coated or dipped in a sauce.
The liver of a cod fish
The claw of a crab

A fishcake (sometimes written as fish cake) is a food item similar to a croquette, consisting of filleted fish or other seafood with potato patty, sometimes coated in breadcrumbs or batter, and fried.

Fishcakes as defined in the Oxford Dictionary of Food and Nutrition are chopped or minced fish mixed with potato, egg and flour with seasonings of onions, peppers and sometimes herbs.

A fish fillet, from the French word filet meaning a thread or strip, is the flesh of a fish which has been cut or sliced away from the bone by cutting lengthwise along one side of the fish parallel to the backbone.
Pet food is plant or animal material intended for consumption by pets.
A mixture of at least two different vegetables.
Mustard greens are leaves from a mustard plant
A white colored seed of a navy bean plant which is a varietal of a common bean plant (Phaseolus vulgaris)
The navy bean is native to the Americas, where it was domesticated.

Spiny lobsters, also known as langustas, langouste, or rock lobsters, are a family (Palinuridae) of about 60 species of achelate crustaceans, in the Decapoda Reptantia. Spiny lobsters are also, especially in Australia, New Zealand, Ireland, South Africa, and the Bahamas, called crayfish, sea crayfish, or crawfish ("kreef" in South Africa), terms which elsewhere are reserved for freshwater crayfish.
A rosette of a romaine lettuce plant (Lactuca sativa var. longifolia).
Romaine or cos lettuce is a variety of lettuce that grows in a tall head of sturdy dark green leaves with firm ribs down their centers. Unlike most lettuces, it is tolerant of heat.
A tropical fruit food product is any fruit product derived from a tropical or subtropical fruit producing plant.
A whole breast that is obtained from a turkey.
Turkey breast consists mainly of the breast meat portion of a turkey, and may or may not include connected bone ("deboned or boneless versus bone-in") and skin.

definition.value: A moth bean food product is a food product derived from the moth bean plant.
The alpaca (Vicugna pacos) is a species of South American camelid.
Canola meal is an oilseed meal made from canola grain.  Canola meal is a by-product of the oil crushing process.
Scallions (also known as green onions, spring onions, or salad onions) are vegetables of various Allium onion species.
An Alpaca meat food product is a meat food product derived from an alpaca
Ampullariidae, common name the apple snails, is a family of large freshwater snails, aquatic gastropod mollusks with a gill and an operculum.
One or more pieces of deboned chicken meat.
A whole breast that is obtained from a chicken.
The breast meat portion of a chicken that may include connected bone and skin.
A whole animal liver that is obtained from a chicken.
A chicken carcass that includes giblets.

The process of cleaning food to separate other environmental materials or body substances.
Food which is the output of a cleaning process.
A raw lung that is obtained from a beef.

Cow lung is used in various cuisines and as a source for pulmonary surfactants. In Peru it is known as bofe. In Southeast Asia, Nasi kuning can be made with cow lung. Paru goreng is fried cow lung Padang food. It is a type of offal. In Indonesia, cow's lung is called paru [wikipedia].
A cracker is a flat, dry baked food typically made with flour. In UK English, crackers are sometimes called water biscuits, savoury biscuits or biscuits.
Dog treat is a category of dog food that encompasses dog biscuits but can also include other chewy food materials like rawhide or bone.
A food  product that is output of a grinding process which consists of breaking up food into smaller pieces.

The grinding of food has a wide range from the fragmentation of larger dry legumes and plant seeds like coffee beans, to the grinding of meat into products like hamburger or sausage. The process may involve a meat grinder, or a pestle and mortar.
A food product made of ground or minced turkey meat
A herring fillet is a fillet cut of herring
A whole drumstick that is obtained from a chicken.
The segment of a chicken's leg between the thigh and tarsus (ankle).
Flies are insects with a pair of functional wings for flight and a pair of specialized hindwings called halteres for balance.
A hulled food is a grain such as rice that has been subjected to a dehulling process.
Dehulling is the process of removing the hulls (or chaff) from beans and other seeds.
Husking of corn is the process of removing its outer layers, leaving only the cob or seed rack of the corn
Mink are dark-colored, semiaquatic, carnivorous mammals of the genera Neovison and Mustela, and part of the family Mustelidae which also includes weasels, otters and ferrets.
A nutritional preparation in powdered form.
Pabda fish is a freshwater catfish species found mainly in the pond, swamp, paddy field etc. in Bangladesh, India, Pakistan, Nepal and some other south Asian countries.
